<subSubSection id="76DA513E966EF948C6D3794D409A3CAE" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8A0E0707832F00FB78686641C1B068B8" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44937D96FD20878BF7C4BA4D3C69B499" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="0939294A1DDC6122A884FA2C978D3F13" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Pasteels" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota leleupi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleupi">
<emphasis id="D29F014A10963CE4CD99BFF6A4FFDDBC" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pampsilota leleupi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="E1C7C3C2821C41EBD906C7B810C964E7" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis id="C3F26832401159621EF06F8AC52A3A96" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pampsilota afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its large body size, thorax without pale makings, and abdomen at least partly pale, but 
<taxonomicName id="7B4C702E5526EC0C73BDEEDD13AB73C8" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Pasteels" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota leleupi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleupi">
<emphasis id="7553EDE762CD59AB2381E01F0AD852D0" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pampsilota leleupi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognised by its extensively pale legs (largely black in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF52CAB07284E26D2DE29DA1CC887A" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis id="C9B61511C0125D757B93C729581416C4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pampsilota afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="75B14EAC5C8C16D5DC51244F64254699" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BCFE505515EEA099F0C31A8006263468" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1DE7ABA7439F3EE1AA7AE8BD56AD23D" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The genitalia preparation mentioned above (&quot;Genit. ♂, H4-47&quot;) was not available (personal communication from Stephane Hanot, collection manager at MRAC, 26.02.2015). The illustration of the penis valve is therefore taken from 
<bibRefCitation id="7CD197CF031C12365FFFF7B2688B666D" author="Pasteels, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 123" refId="B29" refString="Pasteels, J, 1953. Prodromes d'une faune des Tenthredinoidea (Hymenoptera) de l'Afrique noire 1. Argidae. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique 26: 1 - 123" title="Prodromes d'une faune des Tenthredinoidea (Hymenoptera) de l'Afrique noire 1. Argidae." volume="26" year="1953">Pasteels (1953)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
